{
  "text": "Cancer. \ue062ree nested casecontrol studies, included 513 breast cancer patients as compared to 2557 controls, were used to evaluate the risk of breast, colon, and prostate cancers developing in patients exposed to thiazolidinediones (TZDs) as compared with other antidiabetic agents and they showed a neutral effect of TZDs on the likelihood of the development of cancers including colon, prostate, and breast cancers [CITATION_1] .",
